{"title": "Accidentally Broke the MacGuffin", "content": "You had one job Steve! At least he didn't break the Soul Gem, but it disappeared.\n\nThe heroes have finally found the MacGuffin. After so much effort and Your Princess Is in Another Castle!, they're going to return it, use it, or whatever they were supposed to do with it.\n\nThen somebody breaks it, making the whole endeavour pointless.\n\nA particularly frustrating form of a Diabolus ex Machina. The other characters' reactions usually range from shock to an anger burst. Double points if the MacGuffin can NEVER be replaced. In a story where The Good Guys Always Win, if the villain gets their hands on the MacGuffin, it's either taken from them or this happens.\n\nThis usually happens during the middle of the series, not during a Grand Finale which would change the course of who wins. Often used in a \"Shaggy Dog\" Story.\n\nContrast Dismantled MacGuffin, where the MacGuffin is not broken, but is meant to be put back together. Often leads to No MacGuffin, No Winner. This only refers to objects, so a Living MacGuffin (obviously) does not count.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentallyBrokeTheMacGuffin", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheAvengers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JoshScorcher", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/CardCaptorSakura", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/InuYasha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TokyoMewMew", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PokemonHeroes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/JonathanHickmansAvengers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/CerebusTheAardvark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BlackScience", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Cinderella", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/CloudyWithAChanceOfMeatballs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/IceAge", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Zootopia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Apollo13", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BedknobsAndBroomstic